s unintended movements as vital reminders of embodied struggle amid the constraining structures in contemporary culture. Archias also draws compelling comparisons between embodiment as performed in the work of these three artists and in the sit-ins and other nonviolent protests of the era.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aArts, AmericanzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aPerformance artzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aPerformance artistszUnited Statesy20th century. 7aART / Performance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300220438423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300220438.jpg  a978-3-11-066771-4  YUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO